{% extends "partials/_layout.twig" %}

{# Set the page title #}
{% set pageTitle = 'shirahama.town' %}
{% set current_nav = 'about' %}

{% block page %}
	{# Start writing code! #}
	<section class="wide content-page-section">

		<div class="top-column">
			<div class="content">
                <h2>About us</h2>
				<h1>Making T-Shirts the Right Way</h1>
			</div>
		</div>
        <div class="full-column">
            <div class="left-column">
                    <p>
                        We're a small, local company based in Shirahama with a 
                        simple mission: create exceptional t-shirts that this region deserves.
                        <br /><br />
                        The market is flooded with cheap, mass-produced apparel 
                        that falls apart after a few washes. We saw a gap for 
                        something better - high-quality garments that actually 
                        last, made right here in Kansai using Japanese 
                        materials and craftsmanship.
                        <br /><br />
                        Everything happens in-house and on a small scale. We 
                        design each piece ourselves, drawing inspiration from 
                        Shirahama's stunning coastline and natural beauty. We work
                        directly with local suppliers and manufacturers who share
                        our commitment to quality over quantity.
                    </p>
            </div>
            <div class="right-column">
                    <p>
                        The result? T-shirts that feel as good as they look, made by 
                        people who care about what they're creating. No corners cut, 
                        no compromises on materials or construction.
                        <br /><br />
                        We're not trying to compete with fast fashion. We're 
                        building something different, apparel that's worth 
                        owning, made the right way, in small batches, for 
                        people who appreciate the difference quality makes.
                    </p>
            </div>
        </div>

	</section>

{% endblock %}
